        <abstract> 
<p>Has read <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi> with satisfaction. He had long ago come to consider the fixity of species as contrary to the facts, but could see no suitable alternative. The <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi> has brought the light to guide him.</p>  
<p>Sends CD a copy of his latest work ["Mémoire sur la production artificielle des monstruosités", <hi rend="italic">Ann. Sci. Nat. (Zool.)</hi> 4th ser. 18 (1862): 243–76]. Hopes to explain a great number of anomalies by his experimental work on artificially produced monstrosities.</p> 
        </abstract>
